# File Integrity Checker

![Bash](https://img.shields.io/badge/Shell-Bash-4EAA25?logo=gnu-bash)
![Platform](https://img.shields.io/badge/Platform-Linux%20%7C%20macOS%20%7C%20WSL-blue)
![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-green)

A Bash-based tool that monitors file system integrity by comparing current states against recorded baselines, detecting unauthorized modifications, accidental changes, and potential security breaches through comprehensive tracking of:

- File permissions changes
- Ownership modifications
- Size alterations
- Timestamp updates
- Other critical file attributes

## Key Features
🔍 **Baseline Snapshots** - Record directory structures and file metadata  
🛡️ **Change Detection** - Identify modifications against baselines  
📊 **Priority-Based Reporting** - Categorize changes by severity  
⚡ **Lightweight** - Pure Bash implementation with no dependencies  
🔧 **Flexible** - Works on Linux, macOS, and Windows (via WSL/Cygwin)  

